{"title_page": "Kim Leine", "text_new": "[[File:Kim Leine.jpg|thumb|Kim Leine in Leipzig 2014]]\n'''Kim Leine Rasmussen''' (28 August 1961 in [[Seljord]], [[Telemark]]) is a Danish-Norwegian author.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forfatterweb.dk/oversigt/leine-kim/?searchterm=leine%20kim|title=Leine, Kim \u2014 Forfatterweb|publisher=|accessdate=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, he was awarded the [[Nordic Council Literature Prize]] for the novel ''[[The Prophets of Eternal Fjord]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-litteraturpris/media/literature-prizewinners-1962-2013|title=Literature Prizewinners 1962 - 2013|publisher=|accessdate=18 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319235454/http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-litteraturpris/media/literature-prizewinners-1962-2013/|archive-date=19 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jan/16/the-prophets-of-eternal-fjord-kim-leine-review-novel|title=The Prophets of Eternal Fjord by Kim Leine review \u2013 \u2018utterly unpredictable to the very last page\u2019|last=Jensen|first=Liz|date=2016-01-16|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-04-14|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Library|first=The New York Public|title=Kim Leine with Simon Winchester: Arctic Imagination {{!}} LIVE from the NYPL|date=2018-12-12|url=https://vimeo.com/306021344|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cenes.ubc.ca/events/event/lunch-talk-kim-leine-prophets-of-the-eternal-fjord/|title=Book Talk: Kim Leine on \"The Prophets of Eternal Fjord\" {{!}} Central, Eastern, & Northern European Studies|website=cenes.ubc.ca|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\n=== Novels ===\n* ''Kalak'' (2007)\n* ''Valdemarsdag'' (2008)\n* ''Tunu'' (2009)\n* ''Profeterne i Evighedsfjorden'' (2012); English translation: ''[[The Prophets of Eternal Fjord]]''\n* ''Afgrunden'' (2015)\n* ''De s\u00f8vnl\u00f8se'' (2016)\n* ''R\u00f8d mand/Sort mand'' (Gyldendal, 2018)\n\n=== Children's books ===\n* ''Drengen der drog nordp\u00e5 med sin far for at finde julemanden'' (2015), illustrated by Peter Bay Alexandersen\n* ''Skovpigen Sk\u00e6rv'' (2016), illustrated by Peter Bay Alexandersen\n* ''Pigen der kunne tale med hunde'' (2017), illustrated by Peter Bay Alexandersen\n\n=== Comics ===\n* ''Trojka 1: Skarab\u00e6ens time'' (2018), illustrated by S\u00f8ren Mosdal<ref>{{cite web |url=https://forlagetfahrenheit.dk/product/trojka-1-skarabaeens-time/ |title=Trojka 1: Skarab\u00e6ens time |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website= |publisher=Forlaget Fahrenheit |language=Danish |access-date=2019-04-23 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{The Nordic Council's Literature Prize}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leine, Kim}}\n[[Category:Norwegian emigrants to Denmark]]\n[[Category:Danish male novelists]]\n[[Category:People from Telemark]]\n[[Category:Nordic Council Literature Prize winners]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Norwegian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish novelists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male writers]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-writer-stub}}\n{{Norway-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Kim Leine.jpg|thumb|Kim Leine in Leipzig 2014]]\n'''Kim Leine Rasmussen''' (28 August 1961 in [[Seljord]], [[Telemark]]) is a Danish-Norwegian author.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forfatterweb.dk/oversigt/leine-kim/?searchterm=leine%20kim|title=Leine, Kim \u2014 Forfatterweb|publisher=|accessdate=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, he was awarded the [[Nordic Council Literature Prize]] for the novel ''[[The Prophets of Eternal Fjord]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-litteraturpris/media/literature-prizewinners-1962-2013|title=Literature Prizewinners 1962 - 2013|publisher=|accessdate=18 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319235454/http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-litteraturpris/media/literature-prizewinners-1962-2013/|archive-date=19 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jan/16/the-prophets-of-eternal-fjord-kim-leine-review-novel|title=The Prophets of Eternal Fjord by Kim Leine review \u2013 \u2018utterly unpredictable to the very last page\u2019|last=Jensen|first=Liz|date=2016-01-16|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-04-14|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Library|first=The New York Public|title=Kim Leine with Simon Winchester: Arctic Imagination {{!}} LIVE from the NYPL|date=2018-12-12|url=https://vimeo.com/306021344|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cenes.ubc.ca/events/event/lunch-talk-kim-leine-prophets-of-the-eternal-fjord/|title=Book Talk: Kim Leine on \"The Prophets of Eternal Fjord\" {{!}} Central, Eastern, & Northern European Studies|website=cenes.ubc.ca|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\n=== Novels ===\n* ''Kalak'' (2007)\n* ''Valdemarsdag'' (2008)\n* ''Tunu'' (2009)\n* ''Profeterne i Evighedsfjorden'' (2012); English translation: ''[[The Prophets of Eternal Fjord]]''\n* ''Afgrunden'' (2015)\n* ''De s\u00f8vnl\u00f8se'' (2016)\n* ''R\u00f8d mand/Sort mand'' (Gyldendal, 2018)\n\n=== Children's books ===\n* ''Drengen der drog nordp\u00e5 med sin far for at finde julemanden'' (2015), illustrated by Peter Bay Alexandersen\n* ''Skovpigen Sk\u00e6rv'' (2016), illustrated by Peter Bay Alexandersen\n* ''Pigen der kunne tale med hunde'' (2017), illustrated by Peter Bay Alexandersen\n\n=== Comics ===\n* ''Trojka 1: Skarab\u00e6ens time'' (2018), illustrated by S\u00f8ren Mosdal<ref>{{cite web |url=https://forlagetfahrenheit.dk/product/trojka-1-skarabaeens-time/ |title=Trojka 1: Skarab\u00e6ens time |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website= |publisher=Forlaget Fahrenheit |language=Danish |access-date=2019-04-23 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{The Nordic Council's Literature Prize}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leine, Kim}}\n[[Category:Norwegian emigrants to Denmark]]\n[[Category:Danish male novelists]]\n[[Category:People from Telemark]]\n[[Category:Nordic Council Literature Prize winners]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Norwegian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish novelists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-writer-stub}}\n{{Norway-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Leine"}
{"title_page": "Morten Kirkskov", "text_new": "{{short description|Danish actor, theater director, and writer}}\n[[File:Morten Kirkskov.jpg|thumb|photo: Natasha Rydvald 2016]]\n\n'''Morten Kirkskov''' (born 28 March 1963, in S\u00f8nder Omme<ref>http://www.danskefilm.dk/skuespiller/1078.html</ref>) is a [[Danes|Danish]] actor, theatre director and writer. He was appointed artistic director of the [[Royal Danish Playhouse]] for the [[Royal Danish Theatre]]<ref>http://politiken.dk/kultur/scene/article5550242.ece</ref> in [[Copenhagen]] in 2015.\n\n== Career ==\nMorten Kirkskov graduated from drama school at [[Odense Theatre]] in 1990 and has appeared on stage in a number of performances at the [[Royal Danish Theatre]], [[\u00d8stre Gasv\u00e6rk Teater]], [[Aalborg Teater|Aalborg Theatre]] and [[Mungo Park (theatre)|Mungo Park]]. Since 1998 he has been a teacher at the [[Danish National School of Theatre and Contemporary Dance|Danish National School of Theatre]]. He was the artistic manager of the [[Aalborg Teater]] from 2011 to 2015.<ref>http://aalborgteater.dk/teatrets-historie/</ref>\n\nKirkskov is known for his role in the 2001 comedy-drama [[Shake It All About (film)|Shake It All About]] along with several supporting roles in major Danish drama series including [[Borgen (TV series)|Borgen]].\n\nIn 2010, he made his debut as a writer with the autobiographical novel Kapgang,<ref>http://www.gyldendal.dk/forfattere/morten-kirkskov-f50647</ref> which in 2014 was adapted into a feature film with the English title [[Speed Walking]]<ref>http://www.b.dk/kultur/kapgang-sjov-og-sorg-i-sdr.-omme</ref> directed by acclaimed Danish director [[Niels Arden Oplev]].\n\nHe recently directed the critically acclaimed production of [[Eugene O'Neill]]'s [[Long Day's Journey into Night]] at the [[Royal Danish Playhouse]] and won the [[Reumert prize]] for Best Director in 2017.<ref>http://aaretsreumert.dk/\u00e5rets-instrukt\u00f8r-2017</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Kirkskov returned to the stage where he starred in a modern production of [[Ingmar Bergman]]'s [[Scenes from a Marriage]] alongside [[Sofie Gr\u00e5b\u00f8l]] of [[The Killing (Danish TV series)]].<ref>https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ingmar-bergman-should-have-written-for-seinfeld-hlq27t9b9/</ref> The successful production debuted its first international performance in October 2018<ref>https://www.sydneyoperahouse.com/backstage/2018/10/ingmar-bergman-scenes.html</ref> at the [[Sydney Opera House]] in [[Sydney, Australia]], where he shared the stage with acclaimed Danish actress [[Stine Stengade]].\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n\n=== Film ===\n\n*''[[Walk with Me (2016 film)|Walk with Me]]'' (2016)\n*''[[:da:Flaskepost fra P (film)|A Conspiracy of Faith]]'' (2016)\n*''[[Boys on Film|Boys on Film 11 - We Are Animals]]'' (2014)\n*''[[The Keeper of Lost Causes]]'' (2013)\n*''[[A Funny Man]]'' (2011)\n*''[[Daisy Diamond]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Brothers (2004 film)|Brothers]]'' (2004)\n*''The Tenth Muse (TV Movie)'' (2003)\n*''[[Shake It All About (film)|Shake It All About]]'' (2001)\n*''Kuren (TV Movie)'' (2001)\n*''Isle of Darkness'' (1997)\n*''V\u00e6relse 17 (TV Movie)'' (1993)\n\n=== Television ===\n*''[[Herrens Veje]]'' (2018)\n*''[[Greyzone]]'' (2018)\n*''[[The Legacy (TV series)|The Legacy]]'' (2014-2017)\n*''[[Borgen (TV series)|Borgen]]'' (2010-2013)\n*''Lykke'' (2012)\n*''[[Sommer (TV series)|Sommer]]'' (2008)\n*''[[The Eagle (TV series)|The Eagle]]'' (2004-2006)\n*''[[Hotellet]]'' (2001-2002)\n*''Bryggeren '' (1996-1997)\n*''Landsbyen'' (1991-1996)\n\n=== As Writer ===\n\n*''[[Speed Walking]]'' - ''based on the novel Kapgang'' (2014)\n*''[[Rosa Morena (film)|Rosa Morena]]'' (2010)\n*''Three Summers (short)'' (2006)\n{{div col  end}}\n\n== Awards and Prizes ==\n*[[Reumert prize]] for Best Director (2017)\n*Sam Besekov Honorary Award (2009)\n*Ole Haslund's Artist Foundation Honorary Award (2006)\n*Erik Mork Honorary Award (2003)\n*[[Lauritzen Award]] (1997)\n*Olaf Ussing Honorary Award (1997)\n\n== External links ==\n*{{iMDb name|0456778}}\n*{{Danish National Filmography name|108226}}\n*{{Sfdb name|343421}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kirkskov, Morten}}\n[[Category:Danish male television actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male film actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male stage actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male novelists]]\n[[Category:Danish theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Danish theatre managers and producers]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Danish actor, theater director, and writer}}\n[[File:Morten Kirkskov.jpg|thumb|photo: Natasha Rydvald 2016]]\n\n'''Morten Kirkskov''' (born 28 March 1963, in S\u00f8nder Omme<ref>http://www.danskefilm.dk/skuespiller/1078.html</ref>) is a [[Danes|Danish]] actor, theatre director and writer. He was appointed artistic director of the [[Royal Danish Playhouse]] for the [[Royal Danish Theatre]]<ref>http://politiken.dk/kultur/scene/article5550242.ece</ref> in [[Copenhagen]] in 2015.\n\n== Career ==\nMorten Kirkskov graduated from drama school at [[Odense Theatre]] in 1990 and has appeared on stage in a number of performances at the [[Royal Danish Theatre]], [[\u00d8stre Gasv\u00e6rk Teater|\u00d8stre Gasv\u00e6rk Teater]], [[Aalborg Teater|Aalborg Theatre]] and [[Mungo Park (theatre)|Mungo Park]]. Since 1998 he has been a teacher at the [[Danish National School of Theatre and Contemporary Dance|Danish National School of Theatre]]. He was the artistic manager of the [[Aalborg Teater]] from 2011 to 2015.<ref>http://aalborgteater.dk/teatrets-historie/</ref>\n\nKirkskov is known for his role in the 2001 comedy-drama [[Shake It All About (film)|Shake It All About]] along with several supporting roles in major Danish drama series including [[Borgen (TV series)|Borgen]].\n\nIn 2010, he made his debut as a writer with the autobiographical novel Kapgang,<ref>http://www.gyldendal.dk/forfattere/morten-kirkskov-f50647</ref> which in 2014 was adapted into a feature film with the English title [[Speed Walking]]<ref>http://www.b.dk/kultur/kapgang-sjov-og-sorg-i-sdr.-omme</ref> directed by acclaimed Danish director [[Niels Arden Oplev]].\n\nHe recently directed the critically acclaimed production of [[Eugene O'Neill]]'s [[Long Day's Journey into Night]] at the [[Royal Danish Playhouse]] and won the [[Reumert prize]] for Best Director in 2017.<ref>http://aaretsreumert.dk/\u00e5rets-instrukt\u00f8r-2017</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Kirkskov returned to the stage where he starred in a modern production of [[Ingmar Bergman]]'s [[Scenes from a Marriage]] alongside [[Sofie Gr\u00e5b\u00f8l]] of [[The Killing (Danish TV series)]]. <ref>https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ingmar-bergman-should-have-written-for-seinfeld-hlq27t9b9/</ref> The successful production debuted its first international performance in October 2018<ref>https://www.sydneyoperahouse.com/backstage/2018/10/ingmar-bergman-scenes.html</ref> at the [[Sydney Opera House]] in [[Sydney, Australia]], where he shared the stage with acclaimed Danish actress [[Stine Stengade]].\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n\n=== Film ===\n\n*''[[Walk with Me (2016 film)|Walk with Me]]'' (2016)\n*''[[:da:Flaskepost fra P (film)|A Conspiracy of Faith]]'' (2016)\n*''[[Boys on Film|Boys on Film 11 - We Are Animals]]'' (2014)\n*''[[The Keeper of Lost Causes]]'' (2013)\n*''[[A Funny Man]]'' (2011)\n*''[[Daisy Diamond]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Brothers (2004 film)|Brothers]]'' (2004)\n*''The Tenth Muse (TV Movie)'' (2003)\n*''[[Shake It All About (film)|Shake It All About]]'' (2001)\n*''Kuren (TV Movie)'' (2001)\n*''Isle of Darkness'' (1997)\n*''V\u00e6relse 17 (TV Movie)'' (1993)\n<br>\n\n=== Television ===\n*''[[Herrens Veje]]'' (2018)\n*''[[Greyzone]]'' (2018)\n*''[[The Legacy (TV series)|The Legacy]]'' (2014-2017)\n*''[[Borgen (TV series)|Borgen]]'' (2010-2013)\n*''Lykke'' (2012)\n*''[[Sommer (TV series)|Sommer]]'' (2008)\n*''[[The Eagle (TV series)|The Eagle]]'' (2004-2006)\n*''[[Hotellet]]'' (2001-2002)\n*''Bryggeren '' (1996-1997)\n*''Landsbyen'' (1991-1996)\n\n=== As Writer ===\n\n*''[[Speed Walking]]'' - ''based on the novel Kapgang'' (2014)\n*''[[Rosa Morena (film)|Rosa Morena]]'' (2010)\n*''Three Summers (short)'' (2006)\n{{div col  end}}\n\n== Awards and Prizes ==\n*[[Reumert prize]] for Best Director (2017)\n*Sam Besekov Honorary Award (2009)\n*Ole Haslund's Artist Foundation Honorary Award (2006)\n*Erik Mork Honorary Award (2003)\n*[[Lauritzen Award]] (1997)\n*Olaf Ussing Honorary Award (1997)\n\n== External links ==\n*{{iMDb name|0456778}}\n*{{Danish National Filmography name|108226}}\n*{{Sfdb name|343421}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kirkskov, Morten}}\n[[Category:Danish male television actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male film actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male stage actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male novelists]]\n[[Category:Danish theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Danish theatre managers and producers]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morten_Kirkskov"}
{"title_page": "K\u00e5re Johannessen", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = K\u00e5re Johannessen\n| image         = Kaare Johannessen.JPG\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = 1964\n| birth_place   = [[Copenhagen]], Denmark\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = Danish\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Historian, [[curator]], presenter, writer, lecturer\n| years_active  = 1994 \u2013 present\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works =\n| website = {{URL|kaarejohannessen.dk/}}\n}}\n'''K\u00e5re Johannessen''' (born 1964) is a [[Danes|Danish]] historian, writer, lecturer and presenter. He is the former [[curator]] at the museum of [[Trelleborg (Slagelse)|Trelleborg]]<ref>{{cite press release | date = 25 June 1999 | title = Ny leder af museet p\u00e5 Trelleborg | publisher = [[Ritzaus Bureau]] }}</ref> and [[Middelaldercentret]], where he worked from 1994 to 1999 and again from 2004 to 2015.<ref name=\"stopper\">[http://guldborgsundgildet.dk/ViewNew.aspx?id=44 K\u00e5re Stopper]. Guldborgsund Gildet. Retrieved 14 April 2015</ref> Today he is a self-employed historian.<ref name=\"stopper\"/><ref name=\"privatpraksis\">{{cite news |title=Nu springer han ud som \"privatpraktiserende historiker\" |work=Ugeavisen Guldborgsund |publisher=Folketidende Gruppen |date=Uge 5 |page=22 }}</ref> While working at Trelleborg he recreated the Viking game of [[knattleikr]] and injured his knee so badly that he had to use crutches for a time.<ref name=KJ>[http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/om_kaare.html kaarejohannessen.dk: Om Kaare] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128062442/http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/om_kaare.html |date=28 November 2015 }}. Retrieved d. 21/6-2012</ref>\n\nJohannessen has written several non-fiction books about both the [[middle ages]] and the [[viking age]] and historical novels.<ref name=\"skrift\">[http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/skrift.html kaarejohannessen.dk: skrift] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151129081559/http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/skrift.html |date=29 November 2015 }}. Retrieved d. 21/6-2012</ref> Furthermore, he has hosted a series of programs on the regional [[TV \u00d8st]] (sub-channel of [[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV 2]]) about historical location [[Region Zealand]] and he has participated in historical quiz shows such as ''Historiequizzen'' (The History Quiz) on [[DR K]].<ref>23. marts 2013 [http://www.tvnyt.com/artikel/default.asp?id=21584 DR K f\u00e5r en historiequiz], af Stig Hartvig Nielsen, [http://www.tvnyt.com/ tvnyt.com]. Retrieved 18 June 2013</ref> He also acted as historical expert in documentaries and series.<ref name=\"KJtv\">[http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/tv_og_film.html kaarejohannessen.dk: tv og film] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128074332/http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/tv_og_film.html |date=28 November 2015 }}. Retrieved d. 21/6-2012</ref> He is very interested in [[World War I]] and has founded a [[Historical reenactment|reenactment]] group that portraits a group of German soldiers at the [[Western Front (World War I)|Western Front]].<ref>[http://www.westfront1916.dk/ Westfront 1916 \u2013 Reinactment og historisk formidling]. Westfront 1916. Retrieved 2 December 2014</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\nJohannessen has written both fiction and non-fiction and has particularly worked with the [[viking age]] and [[middle ages]].<ref name=\"skrift\"/><ref>[http://bibliografi.dk/content.php?page=author&value=13632 Bibliografi.dk \u2013 K\u00e5re Johannessen] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090208203031/http://bibliografi.dk/content.php?page=author&value=13632 |date=8 February 2009 }}. Retrieved 18 June 2013</ref>\n\n* 1993 ''Den hedenske islandske tvekamp'', ([[Syddansk Universitet]], Center for Historie)\n* 1995 ''Den milit\u00e6re udrustning i Bayeux-tapetet''\n* 1997 ''Magi og Heksetro i Nordisk Middelalder'' ([[Middelaldercentret]]) {{ISBN|87-984133-8-4}}\n* 1998 ''Den Sk\u00e6ve Pind \u2013 Buen som Milit\u00e6rv\u00e5ben i Middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret) {{ISBN|978-87-984-1337-0}}\n* 1998 ''Hor Saa Vide \u2013 Seksualiteten i Middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret) {{ISBN|87-984133-9-2}}\n* 2001 ''Politikens Bog om Danmarks Vikingetid'' ([[Politikens Forlag]]) {{ISBN|978-87-567-6456-8}}\n* 2003 ''Blandt Krigere, S\u00f8folk og Tr\u00e6lle \u2013 Vikingetid i Danmark'' ([[Forlaget Klematis]]) {{ISBN|978-87-7905-755-5}}\n* 2003 \"Blod, sved og latter: et benknusende boldspil genskabes\" p.&nbsp;4\u201310 ''Siden Saxo'' \u00c5rg. 20, nr. 1<ref>[https://bibliotek.dk/da/work/870971-tsart:87540014 Blod, sved og latter : et benknusende boldspil genskabes]. [[Bibliotek.dk]]. Retrieved 14 April 2015</ref>\n* 2004 ''Det Lo De Meget Af \u2013 Middelalderens humor'' (Middelaldercentret)\n* 2004 ''Hvad M\u00f8nten Fort\u00e6ller \u2013 en introduktion'' (Middelaldercentret)\n* 2006 ''Stil og Status \u2013 m\u00f8bler og boligindretning i middelalderens verdslige bygninger'' (Middelaldercentret) {{ISBN|978-87-990421-4-2}}\n* 2007 \"Instant Justice? A note on the holmgangslaw of Kormaks Saga\", ''Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Historisches Waffen-und Kleiderkunde''\n* 2008 ''Blodsb\u00e5nd'' (''[[Sl\u00e6gten]]'', 7th installment, [[Aschehoug Dansk Forlag|Aschehoug]]) {{ISBN|978-87-112-9279-2}}\n* 2008 ''Vredens Dag'' (''Sl\u00e6gten'', 9th installment, [[Lindhardt & Ringhof]]) {{ISBN|978-87-7089-205-6}}\n* 2009 ''Forr\u00e6deren'' (''Sl\u00e6gten'', 12th installment, Lindhardt & Ringhof) {{ISBN|9788711421574}}\n* 2009 ''Kejserh\u00f8gen'' ([[Borgens Forlag]]) {{ISBN|9788721035563}}\n* 2011 ''Blandt Sp\u00f8gelser, Gengangere og Andet Godtfolk \u2013 om det overnaturlige i middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret)\n* 2011 ''Guds Dilletanter... og Hvermands \u2013 teater i middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret)\n\n== Filmography ==\n* 2009 ''[[12 Paces Without a Head]]'', German movie\n* 2010 ''En God Historie'' ([[Tv2 \u00f8st]], documentary)\n* 2011 ''Historien om en K\u00f8bstad'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, documentary)\n* 2013 ''[[K\u00e5res Danmarkshistorie]]'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, documentary)\n* 2013\u20132015 ''[[Historiequizzen]]'' ([[DR K]], quiz show)\n* 2013 ''K\u00e5re kigger p\u00e5 Kunst'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, documentary)\n* 2013 ''Vikingeborgen Trelleborg'' ([[dk4]], documentary)\n* 2014 ''I krig for Danmark'' episode 2 og 6 ([[DR K]], documentary)\n* 2014 ''Duellen'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, quiz show)\n* 2015 ''Det danske Guld'' ([[DR K]], documentary)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20151128042530/http://kaarejohannessen.dk/index.html kaarejohannessen.dk] \u2013 Official website\n*[http://www.westfront1916.dk/ Westfront 1916] \u2013 Reenactment group\n*[http://middelaldercentret.dk/ Middelaldercentret.dk] \u2013 Official website of [[Middelaldercentret]]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Johannessen, Kare}}\n[[Category:Danish historians]]\n[[Category:Danish curators]]\n[[Category:Danish non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Danish male novelists]]\n[[Category:Danish television presenters]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = K\u00e5re Johannessen\n| image         = Kaare Johannessen.JPG\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = 1964\n| birth_place   = [[Copenhagen]], Denmark\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = Danish\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Historian, [[curator]], presenter, writer, lecturer\n| years_active  = 1994 \u2013 present\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works =\n| website = {{URL|kaarejohannessen.dk/}}\n}}\n'''K\u00e5re Johannessen''' (born 1964) is a [[Danes|Danish]] historian, writer, lecturer and presenter. He is the former [[curator]] at the museum of [[Trelleborg (Slagelse)|Trelleborg]]<ref>{{cite press release | date = 25 June 1999 | title = Ny leder af museet p\u00e5 Trelleborg | publisher = [[Ritzaus Bureau]] }}</ref> and [[Middelaldercentret]], where he worked from 1994 to 1999 and again from 2004 to 2015.<ref name=\"stopper\">[http://guldborgsundgildet.dk/ViewNew.aspx?id=44 K\u00e5re Stopper]. Guldborgsund Gildet. Retrieved 14 April 2015</ref> Today he is a self-employed historian.<ref name=\"stopper\"/><ref name=\"privatpraksis\">{{cite news |title=Nu springer han ud som \"privatpraktiserende historiker\" |work=Ugeavisen Guldborgsund |publisher=Folketidende Gruppen |date=Uge 5 |page=22 }}</ref> While working at Trelleborg he recreated the Viking game of [[knattleikr]] and injured his knee so badly that he had to use crutches for a time.<ref name=KJ>[http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/om_kaare.html kaarejohannessen.dk: Om Kaare] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128062442/http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/om_kaare.html |date=28 November 2015 }}. Retrieved d. 21/6-2012</ref>\n\nJohannessen has written several non-fiction books about both the [[middle ages]] and the [[viking age]] and historical novels.<ref name=\"skrift\">[http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/skrift.html kaarejohannessen.dk: skrift] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151129081559/http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/skrift.html |date=29 November 2015 }}. Retrieved d. 21/6-2012</ref> Furthermore, he has hosted a series of programs on the regional [[TV \u00d8st]] (sub-channel of [[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV 2]]) about historical location [[Region Zealand]] and he has participated in historical quiz shows such as ''Historiequizzen'' (The History Quiz) on [[DR K]].<ref>23. marts 2013 [http://www.tvnyt.com/artikel/default.asp?id=21584 DR K f\u00e5r en historiequiz], af Stig Hartvig Nielsen, [http://www.tvnyt.com/ tvnyt.com]. Retrieved 18 June 2013</ref> He also acted as historical expert in documentaries and series.<ref name=\"KJtv\">[http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/tv_og_film.html kaarejohannessen.dk: tv og film] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128074332/http://www.kaarejohannessen.dk/tv_og_film.html |date=28 November 2015 }}. Retrieved d. 21/6-2012</ref> He is very interested in [[World War I]] and has founded a [[Historical reenactment|reenactment]] group that portraits a group of German soldiers at the [[Western Front (World War I)|Western Front]].<ref>[http://www.westfront1916.dk/ Westfront 1916 \u2013 Reinactment og historisk formidling]. Westfront 1916. Retrieved 2 December 2014</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\nJohannessen has written both fiction and non-fiction and has particularly worked with the [[viking age]] and [[middle ages]].<ref name=\"skrift\"/><ref>[http://bibliografi.dk/content.php?page=author&value=13632 Bibliografi.dk \u2013 K\u00e5re Johannessen] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090208203031/http://bibliografi.dk/content.php?page=author&value=13632 |date=8 February 2009 }}. Retrieved 18 June 2013</ref>\n\n* 1993 ''Den hedenske islandske tvekamp'', ([[Syddansk Universitet]], Center for Historie)\n* 1995 ''Den milit\u00e6re udrustning i Bayeux-tapetet''\n* 1997 ''Magi og Heksetro i Nordisk Middelalder'' ([[Middelaldercentret]]) {{ISBN|87-984133-8-4}}\n* 1998 ''Den Sk\u00e6ve Pind \u2013 Buen som Milit\u00e6rv\u00e5ben i Middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret) {{ISBN|978-87-984-1337-0}}\n* 1998 ''Hor Saa Vide \u2013 Seksualiteten i Middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret) {{ISBN|87-984133-9-2}}\n* 2001 ''Politikens Bog om Danmarks Vikingetid'' ([[Politikens Forlag]]) {{ISBN|978-87-567-6456-8}}\n* 2003 ''Blandt Krigere, S\u00f8folk og Tr\u00e6lle \u2013 Vikingetid i Danmark'' ([[Forlaget Klematis]]) {{ISBN|978-87-7905-755-5}}\n* 2003 \"Blod, sved og latter: et benknusende boldspil genskabes\" p.&nbsp;4\u201310 ''Siden Saxo'' \u00c5rg. 20, nr. 1<ref>[https://bibliotek.dk/da/work/870971-tsart:87540014 Blod, sved og latter : et benknusende boldspil genskabes]. [[Bibliotek.dk]]. Retrieved 14 April 2015</ref>\n* 2004 ''Det Lo De Meget Af \u2013 Middelalderens humor'' (Middelaldercentret)\n* 2004 ''Hvad M\u00f8nten Fort\u00e6ller \u2013 en introduktion'' (Middelaldercentret)\n* 2006 ''Stil og Status \u2013 m\u00f8bler og boligindretning i middelalderens verdslige bygninger'' (Middelaldercentret) {{ISBN|978-87-990421-4-2}}\n* 2007 \"Instant Justice? A note on the holmgangslaw of Kormaks Saga\", ''Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Historisches Waffen-und Kleiderkunde''\n* 2008 ''Blodsb\u00e5nd'' (''[[Sl\u00e6gten]]'', 7th installment, [[Aschehoug Dansk Forlag|Aschehoug]]) {{ISBN|978-87-112-9279-2}}\n* 2008 ''Vredens Dag'' (''Sl\u00e6gten'', 9th installment, [[Lindhardt & Ringhof]]) {{ISBN|978-87-7089-205-6}}\n* 2009 ''Forr\u00e6deren'' (''Sl\u00e6gten'', 12th installment, Lindhardt & Ringhof) {{ISBN|9788711421574}}\n* 2009 ''Kejserh\u00f8gen'' ([[Borgens Forlag]]) {{ISBN|9788721035563}}\n* 2011 ''Blandt Sp\u00f8gelser, Gengangere og Andet Godtfolk \u2013 om det overnaturlige i middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret)\n* 2011 ''Guds Dilletanter... og Hvermands \u2013 teater i middelalderen'' (Middelaldercentret)\n\n== Filmography ==\n* 2009 ''[[12 Paces Without a Head]]'', German movie\n* 2010 ''En God Historie'' ([[Tv2 \u00f8st]], documentary)\n* 2011 ''Historien om en K\u00f8bstad'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, documentary)\n* 2013 ''[[K\u00e5res Danmarkshistorie]]'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, documentary)\n* 2013\u20132015 ''[[Historiequizzen]]'' ([[DR K]], quiz show)\n* 2013 ''K\u00e5re kigger p\u00e5 Kunst'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, documentary)\n* 2013 ''Vikingeborgen Trelleborg'' ([[dk4]], documentary)\n* 2014 ''I krig for Danmark'' episode 2 og 6 ([[DR K]], documentary)\n* 2014 ''Duellen'' (Tv2 \u00f8st, quiz show)\n* 2015 ''Det danske Guld'' ([[DR K]], documentary)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20151128042530/http://kaarejohannessen.dk/i