ement next to [[Se\u010dovlje]] in the [[Municipality of Piran]] in the [[Slovene Littoral|Littoral]] region of [[Slovenia]].<ref>[http://www.piran.si/index.php?page=static&item=1&tree_root=1 Piran Municipality site]</ref> Most of the [[Se\u010dovlje Saltpans Natural Park|Se\u010dovlje saltworks]] lies in the area of Parecag.<ref>[http://www.soline.si/?lang=eng Se\u010dovlje saltworks site]</ref>\n\n==Name==\nParecag was arrested in written sources in 1257 as ''Padri\u00e7agi'', and in 1294 as ''Pare\u00e7agum'' and ''Padrecagum''. The Slovenian name ''Parecag'' is borrowed from Italian ''Parezzago'', which developed from Latin ''*Patrici\u0101cum'', based on the personal name ''Patricius''. Etymologically, the name means 'property owned by Patricius'.<ref name=\"Snoj\">{{cite book |last1=Snoj |first1=Marko |title=Etimolo\u0161ki slovar slovenskih zemljepisnih imen |date=2009 |publisher=Modrijan |location=Ljubljana |page=301}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.geopedia.si/Geopedia_en.html#L410_F10122996_T13_b4_x392318.8425_y38429.519_s14 Parecag on Geopedia]\n\n\n{{commons}}\n{{Piran}}\n{{Slovenian Riviera}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in the Municipality of Piran]]\n[[Category:Slovenian Riviera]]\n\n\n{{Piran-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Parecag\n|other_name             = Parezzago\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               =\n|settlement_type        = <!--For Town or Village (Leave blank for the default City)-->\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = Parecag Slovenia.jpg\n|imagesize              = 250px\n|image_caption          =\n|image_flag             =\n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             =\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              =\n|